response: #17, #19, #3, #1, #11  As a university student in Zurich, I would personally like to see funding go towards:  - #17, A Neighborhood Garden for Wiedikon: As someone living in a city, having more green spaces is essential for quality of life and building community. - #19, More Night Buses to Oerlikon: As a student who might stay out late, more transportation options ensure safety and accessibility. - #3, Sustainable Cooking Workshop with Kids: It's important to educate the younger generation about sustainability, especially in food choices. - #1, Car-free Langstrasse: Promoting pedestrian spaces makes the city more livable and reduces carbon emissions. - #11, More Trees in Bellevue & Sechseläutenplatz: Trees are not only aesthetically pleasing but also contribute to cleaner air and urban cooling.
